FBIS4-63015 "drsov097_b_94038" FBIS-SOV-94-097 Daily Report 18 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Labor Minister Notes Unemployment in Defense Sector Labor Minister Notes Unemployment in Defense Sector MK1805131094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 18 May 94 p 2 MK1805131094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA Russian BFN [Unattributed report under the "In Brief" rubric] [Text] Izhevsk -- Hidden unemployment at Russia's defense complex enterprises now tops 10 percent while it is 6 percent on average around the country, Russian Federation Labor Minister Gennadiy Melikyan told a RIA correspondent. He pointed out that military-industrial complex enterprises cut back the output of military products by 65 percent over the recent year. In the minister's estimate, 1.4 million of the 70.5 million able-bodied citizens of Russia have been registered to date as officially unemployed with 4.45 million categorized among those who need to be set up in employment.
